Airport closure to international flights
In response to COVID-19, at a press conference by the Ministerial Task Force in Guyana, the Director-General of the Civil Aviation Authority in Guyana announced the closure to all international flights from the Cheddi Jagan International Airport at Timehri and the Eugene Correia Airport at Ogle. The closure started on 17 March 2020 and is scheduled to last for 14 days.
Borders
On 19 March the Government of Brazil announced that it was closing its borders for 15 days with neighbouring countries, including Guyana. The action was taken as a result of the spread of the coronavirus. This measure will be applied to foreigners wishing to enter Brazil, it does not apply to Brazilians wishing to return to the country.
Guidance for travellers coming to Guyana from a COVID-19 affected country is available from the Guyana Ministry of Public Health. The Guyana government hot line is +592 624 3067 and +592 227 4986 ext 215.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
